


15,01                              12Passage

15,01                      12Freely I have come here
15,01                      12to churn in the vast expanse of water & wind,
15,01                      12tiller rising clear on swell crests,
15,01                      12wind rifting the lines...
15,01                      12I take on water & displace more,
15,01                      12my clearance grows slim.
15,01                      12I submerge & surface
15,01                      12gleaming in the low light
15,01                      12as the clouds tumble in,
15,01                      12great swells roil beneath the skiff,
15,01                      12& I look to the shore,
15,01                      12its sumptuous spread,
15,01                      12the great arms of the bay.



